{
  "texts": [
    "And in 2022, ESM2 was trained using masked language modeling over millions of different natural protein evolutions with up to 15 B.",
    "During training, protein sequences are presented to the model with a portion of the residues masked, randomly aligned to different amino acids, or left unmodified.",
    "The task of the model is to predict those masked residues in a bidirectional context of all unmasked residues in the input.",
    "Compared to traditional RNN and LSTM models, RoBERTa is able to execute concurrently, improving the computational efficiency of the model.",
    "However, static masking may result in the model not being able to adequately adapt to different masking strategies."
  ]
}